[2026-03-07T18:49:50Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012uHU5wr2SMuKTi5y43q4Vk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of the orchestration flow:\n\n## Orchestration Flow Summary\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here is the complete orchestration flow in the Cloche project:\n\n### 1. **Entry Points**\n\n#### CLI Command: `cloche orchestrate`\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 396-408)\n\n```go\nfunc cmdOrchestrate(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient) {\n\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n\tresp, err := client.Orchestrate(ctx, &pb.OrchestrateRequest{ProjectDir: cwd})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tif resp.Dispatched == 0 {\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"No ready work found.\")  // <-- Message originates here\n\t} else {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Dispatched %d run(s).\\n\", resp.Dispatched)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\nThe **\"No ready work found\"** message originates in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` at line 404, printed when the gRPC response has `Dispatched == 0`.\n\n#### gRPC Service Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 13, 73-79)\n\n```proto\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc Orchestrate(OrchestrateRequest) returns (OrchestrateResponse);\n  // ...\n}\n\nmessage OrchestrateRequest {\n  string project_dir = 1;\n}\n\nmessage OrchestrateResponse {\n  int32 dispatched = 1;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **gRPC Handler (Daemon-side)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 668-677)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) Orchestrate(ctx context.Context, req *pb.OrchestrateRequest) (*pb.OrchestrateResponse, error) {\n\tif s.orchestrateFn == nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"orchestrator not configured\")\n\t}\n\tdispatched, err := s.orchestrateFn(ctx, req.ProjectDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"orchestration failed: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn &pb.OrchestrateResponse{Dispatched: int32(dispatched)}, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe gRPC handler delegates to `s.orchestrateFn`, which is set up in the daemon initialization.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Daemon Initialization (Orchestrator Setup)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 226-285)\n\nKey flow:\n- Initializes an `orchestrator.Orchestrator` instance\n- Registers all projects with orchestration enabled (reads from their `.cloche/config.yaml`)\n- Sets up gRPC callbacks:\n  - `SetOnRunComplete`: Callback when a run finishes (line 79-81)\n  - `SetOrchestrateFunc`: Function invoked by the Orchestrate RPC (line 82-87)\n\n```go\nfunc initOrchestrator(globalCfg *config.Config, store ports.RunStore, srv *adaptgrpc.ClocheServer) *orchestrator.Orchestrator {\n\t// ...\n\torch := orchestrator.New(promptGen, dispatch, /* options */)\n\t\n\t// Register all projects with orchestration enabled\n\tfor dir := range candidates {\n\t\tcfg, err := config.Load(dir)\n\t\tif err != nil || !cfg.Orchestration.Enabled {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\ttracker := beads.NewTracker(dir)  // <-- Task tracker (beads)\n\t\torch.Register(&orchestrator.ProjectConfig{\n\t\t\tDir:         dir,\n\t\t\tWorkflow:    cfg.Orchestration.Workflow,\n\t\t\tConcurrency: cfg.Orchestration.Concurrency,\n\t\t\tTracker:     tracker,\n\t\t})\n\t\tregistered++\n\t}\n\t// ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Core Orchestrator Logic**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`\n\n#### Data Structures\n\n```go\ntype Orchestrator struct {\n\t// ... other fields ...\n\tprojects           map[string]*ProjectConfig // keyed by Dir\n\tinFlight           map[string]int            // keyed by Dir: count of running tasks\n\tinFlightTasks      map[string]string         // runID -> taskID\n\tinFlightTaskSet    map[string]map[string]bool // projectDir -> set of taskIDs in flight\n\t// ...\n}\n\ntype ProjectConfig struct {\n\tDir         string\n\tWorkflow    string\n\tConcurrency int\n\tTracker     ports.TaskTracker  // <-- Points to beads tracker\n\tEnabled     bool\n}\n```\n\n#### Main Orchestration Cycle: `Run()`\n**Lines:** 169-300\n\nThe orchestrator follows this algorithm:\n\n1. **Lock and Check State** (169-182):\n   - Get project config\n   - Calculate available concurrency slots: `available = Concurrency - inFlight[projectDir]`\n\n2. **Determine \"Ready Work\"** (188-191):\n   ```go\n   tasks, err := pc.Tracker.ListReady(ctx, projectDir)\n   ```\n   - Calls the task tracker's `ListReady()` to get open tasks with no blocking dependencies\n   - Ready tasks are returned sorted by priority (highest first)\n\n3. **Check Available Slots** (184-186):\n   ```go\n   if available <= 0 {\n       return 0, nil  // No capacity → return 0 dispatched\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Process Ready Tasks** (203-297):\n   For each ready task (up to `available` slots):\n   \n   a. **Skip if Already In-Flight** (207-213):\n   ```go\n   alreadyRunning := o.isTaskInFlight(projectDir, task.ID)\n   if alreadyRunning {\n       log.Printf(\"orchestrator: skipping task %s (already in flight)\", task.ID)\n       continue\n   }\n   ```\n   \n   b. **Claim the Task** (215-218):\n   ```go\n   if err := pc.Tracker.Claim(ctx, task.ID); err != nil {\n       log.Printf(\"orchestrator: failed to claim task %s: %v\", task.ID, err)\n       continue\n   }\n   ```\n   \n   c. **Two Execution Paths**:\n   \n   **Path A: Host Workflow** (220-272)\n   - If `.cloche/host.cloche` exists:\n     - Parse the workflow\n     - Execute it with `HostRunner.RunWorkflow()`\n     - Increment `inFlight[projectDir]` and track task\n     - Run in background goroutine\n   \n   **Path B: Fallback (Prompt → Dispatch)** (274-296)\n     - Generate prompt via `promptGen.Generate()`\n     - Dispatch run via `dispatch()` (which calls `srv.RunWorkflow()`)\n     - Increment `inFlight[projectDir]` and track task\n\n5. **Return Dispatched Count** (299):\n   ```go\n   return dispatched, nil\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **In-Flight Tracking**\n\n**Data Structures:**\n- `inFlight[projectDir]`: Integer count of running tasks per project\n- `inFlightTasks[runID]`: Maps run ID to task ID (for completion handling)\n- `inFlightTaskSet[projectDir][taskID]`: Set-like map for fast deduplication checks\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n```go\n// trackTask (lines 141-147): Record a new in-flight task\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) trackTask(projectDir, runID, taskID string) {\n\to.inFlightTasks[runID] = taskID\n\tif o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] == nil {\n\t\to.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] = make(map[string]bool)\n\t}\n\to.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir][taskID] = true\n}\n\n// untrackTask (lines 150-157): Remove when task completes\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) untrackTask(projectDir, runID string) string {\n\ttaskID := o.inFlightTasks[runID]\n\tdelete(o.inFlightTasks, runID)\n\tif taskID != \"\" && o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] != nil {\n\t\tdelete(o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir], taskID)\n\t}\n\treturn taskID\n}\n\n// isTaskInFlight (lines 160-165): Check if task is already running (deduplication)\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) isTaskInFlight(projectDir, taskID string) bool {\n\tif set := o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir]; set != nil {\n\t\treturn set[taskID]\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n\n// InFlight (lines 353-357): Public method to query current in-flight count\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) InFlight(projectDir string) int {\n\to.mu.Lock()\n\tdefer o.mu.Unlock()\n\treturn o.inFlight[projectDir]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Concurrency Limit Determination**\n\nThe orchestrator determines \"ready work\" based on:\n\n1. **Available Concurrency Slots**:\n   ```\n   available = ProjectConfig.Concurrency - inFlight[projectDir]\n   ```\n   - If `available <= 0`, no new tasks are dispatched (returns 0)\n\n2. **Task Readiness** (from beads tracker):\n   - Tasks must have status == \"open\"\n   - All blocking dependencies must be \"closed\"\n   - No in-flight task with the same ID (deduplication)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Beads Task Tracker**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go`\n\nThe tracker manages open tasks in `.beads/issues.jsonl`:\n\n```go\ntype Tracker struct {\n\tprojectDir string\n\tmu         sync.Mutex\n}\n\n// ListReady returns open tasks whose blocking dependencies are all closed\nfunc (t *Tracker) ListReady(ctx context.Context, project string) ([]ports.TrackerTask, error) {\n\t// 1. Read all issues from .beads/issues.jsonl\n\tissues, err := readIssuesFromFile(t.beadsPath())\n\t\n\t// 2. Build status lookup\n\tstatusByID := make(map[string]string, len(issues))\n\tfor _, iss := range issues {\n\t\tstatusByID[iss.ID] = iss.Status\n\t}\n\t\n\t// 3. Filter: open status + all dependencies closed\n\tvar tasks []ports.TrackerTask\n\tfor _, iss := range issues {\n\t\tif iss.Status != \"open\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tif hasOpenBlockers(iss, statusByID) {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\ttasks = append(tasks, ports.TrackerTask{...})\n\t}\n\t\n\t// 4. Sort by priority (highest first)\n\tsort.Slice(tasks, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\treturn tasks[i].Priority > tasks[j].Priority\n\t})\n\t\n\treturn tasks, nil\n}\n\n// Claim, Complete, Fail: Update task status by appending to JSONL\nfunc (t *Tracker) Claim(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error {\n\treturn t.appendStatusUpdate(taskID, \"in_progress\")\n}\n\nfunc (t *Tracker) Complete(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error {\n\treturn t.appendStatusUpdate(taskID, \"closed\")\n}\n\nfunc (t *Tracker) Fail(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error {\n\treturn t.appendStatusUpdate(taskID, \"open\")  // Retry\n}\n```\n\n**Port Interface:**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/tracker.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskTracker interface {\n\tListReady(ctx context.Context, project string) ([]TrackerTask, error)\n\tClaim(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n\tComplete(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n\tFail(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Run Completion and Auto-Trigger**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` (lines 327-350)\n\nWhen a workflow run completes:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) OnRunComplete(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, runID string, state domain.RunState) {\n\t// 1. Untrack the task and decrement in-flight counter\n\to.mu.Lock()\n\tpc := o.projects[projectDir]\n\ttaskID := o.untrackTask(projectDir, runID)\n\tif o.inFlight[projectDir] > 0 {\n\t\to.inFlight[projectDir]--\n\t}\n\to.mu.Unlock()\n\n\t// 2. Update task status in tracker\n\tif taskID != \"\" && pc != nil {\n\t\tif state == domain.RunStateSucceeded {\n\t\t\t_ = pc.Tracker.Complete(ctx, taskID)\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t_ = pc.Tracker.Fail(ctx, taskID)  // Reset to \"open\" for retry\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// 3. Trigger new orchestration cycle (auto-dispatch waiting tasks)\n\tif _, err := o.Run(ctx, projectDir); err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"orchestrator: post-completion trigger failed for %s: %v\", projectDir, err)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**Callback Registration:**\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 79-81)\n\n```go\nsrv.SetOnRunComplete(func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, runID string, state domain.RunState) {\n\torch.OnRunComplete(ctx, projectDir, runID, state)\n})\n```\n\nWhen a run completes, the gRPC server (in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, line 318) calls this callback.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Startup Auto-Trigger**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 139-146)\n\n```go\n// Trigger orchestration on startup\nif orch != nil {\n\tgo func() {\n\t\tn := orch.TriggerAll(context.Background())\n\t\tif n > 0 {\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"startup: orchestrator dispatched %d run(s)\\n\", n)\n\t\t}\n\t}()\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Web Dashboard Integration**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe web dashboard provides real-time control and monitoring:\n\n- **POST /api/projects/{name}/trigger**: Trigger orchestration (line 148)\n- **GET /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator**: Get status (enabled, in_flight, concurrency) (line 149)\n- **POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start**: Enable orchestration (line 150)\n- **POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop**: Disable orchestration (line 151)\n- **POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency**: Set concurrency limit (line 152)\n\nKey handler:\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIOrchestratorStatus(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif h.orchestrator == nil {\n\t\t// ...\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tenabled, inFlight, concurrency := h.orchestrator.Status(dir)\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]any{\n\t\t\"enabled\":     enabled,\n\t\t\"in_flight\":   inFlight,\n\t\t\"concurrency\": concurrency,\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Complete Message Flow (Summary)**\n\n```\ncloche orchestrate (CLI)\n       ↓\ngRPC Orchestrate(OrchestrateRequest)\n       ↓\nClocheServer.Orchestrate()\n       ↓\norchestrateFn = Orchestrator.Run(projectDir) or Orchestrator.TriggerAll()\n       ↓\nOrchestrator.Run():\n  1. Lock and check if available slots exist\n  2. Call TaskTracker.ListReady() → beads tracker reads .beads/issues.jsonl\n  3. For each ready task (up to available slots):\n     - Skip if task already in-flight (deduplication)\n     - Call Tracker.Claim(taskID) → marks as \"in_progress\"\n     - Check for .cloche/host.cloche:\n       a) If exists → HostRunner.RunWorkflow()\n       b) Otherwise → PromptGen.Generate() → Dispatch()\n     - Increment inFlight[projectDir]\n     - Track task: inFlightTasks[runID] = taskID\n  4. Return dispatched count\n       ↓\ngRPC response: OrchestrateResponse{Dispatched: count}\n       ↓\nCLI prints \"No ready work found\" (if count == 0) or \"Dispatched N run(s)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 12. **File Reference Map**\n\n| Component | File Path |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| CLI Entry | `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (cmdOrchestrate, line 396) |\n| Proto Definition | `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` |\n| gRPC Handler | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (Orchestrate, line 668) |\n| Orchestrator Core | `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` |\n| Beads Tracker | `/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go` |\n| Tracker Port | `/workspace/internal/ports/tracker.go` |\n| Daemon Init | `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (initOrchestrator, line 226) |\n| Web Handlers | `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 674-937) |\n| HostRunner | `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go` |\n| Tests | `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator_test.go` |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abe38294998f00624 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 72253\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 54432</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36e135ce-10f3-4a37-be7d-4cf1fde5dba1","uuid":"2c67ad89-e7f3-4e13-b0fb-e8447e6ead41","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the orchestration flow in this Go project. Specifically:\n\n1. Find all files related to \"orchestrate\" or \"orchestrator\" - the gRPC handler, daemon-side logic, and any in-flight tracking\n2. Find the beads tracker / \"bd list\" functionality that lists open tasks\n3. Find where \"No ready work found\" message originates\n4. Find the concurrency/inFlight tracking logic\n5. Find how the orchestrator determines \"ready work\"\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely. I need to understand the full flow from the CLI command through gRPC to the daemon-side orchestrator logic.","agentId":"abe38294998f00624","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of the orchestration flow:\n\n## Orchestration Flow Summary\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here is the complete orchestration flow in the Cloche project:\n\n### 1. **Entry Points**\n\n#### CLI Command: `cloche orchestrate`\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 396-408)\n\n```go\nfunc cmdOrchestrate(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient) {\n\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n\tresp, err := client.Orchestrate(ctx, &pb.OrchestrateRequest{ProjectDir: cwd})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tif resp.Dispatched == 0 {\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"No ready work found.\")  // <-- Message originates here\n\t} else {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Dispatched %d run(s).\\n\", resp.Dispatched)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\nThe **\"No ready work found\"** message originates in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` at line 404, printed when the gRPC response has `Dispatched == 0`.\n\n#### gRPC Service Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 13, 73-79)\n\n```proto\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc Orchestrate(OrchestrateRequest) returns (OrchestrateResponse);\n  // ...\n}\n\nmessage OrchestrateRequest {\n  string project_dir = 1;\n}\n\nmessage OrchestrateResponse {\n  int32 dispatched = 1;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **gRPC Handler (Daemon-side)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 668-677)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) Orchestrate(ctx context.Context, req *pb.OrchestrateRequest) (*pb.OrchestrateResponse, error) {\n\tif s.orchestrateFn == nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"orchestrator not configured\")\n\t}\n\tdispatched, err := s.orchestrateFn(ctx, req.ProjectDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"orchestration failed: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn &pb.OrchestrateResponse{Dispatched: int32(dispatched)}, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe gRPC handler delegates to `s.orchestrateFn`, which is set up in the daemon initialization.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Daemon Initialization (Orchestrator Setup)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 226-285)\n\nKey flow:\n- Initializes an `orchestrator.Orchestrator` instance\n- Registers all projects with orchestration enabled (reads from their `.cloche/config.yaml`)\n- Sets up gRPC callbacks:\n  - `SetOnRunComplete`: Callback when a run finishes (line 79-81)\n  - `SetOrchestrateFunc`: Function invoked by the Orchestrate RPC (line 82-87)\n\n```go\nfunc initOrchestrator(globalCfg *config.Config, store ports.RunStore, srv *adaptgrpc.ClocheServer) *orchestrator.Orchestrator {\n\t// ...\n\torch := orchestrator.New(promptGen, dispatch, /* options */)\n\t\n\t// Register all projects with orchestration enabled\n\tfor dir := range candidates {\n\t\tcfg, err := config.Load(dir)\n\t\tif err != nil || !cfg.Orchestration.Enabled {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\ttracker := beads.NewTracker(dir)  // <-- Task tracker (beads)\n\t\torch.Register(&orchestrator.ProjectConfig{\n\t\t\tDir:         dir,\n\t\t\tWorkflow:    cfg.Orchestration.Workflow,\n\t\t\tConcurrency: cfg.Orchestration.Concurrency,\n\t\t\tTracker:     tracker,\n\t\t})\n\t\tregistered++\n\t}\n\t// ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Core Orchestrator Logic**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`\n\n#### Data Structures\n\n```go\ntype Orchestrator struct {\n\t// ... other fields ...\n\tprojects           map[string]*ProjectConfig // keyed by Dir\n\tinFlight           map[string]int            // keyed by Dir: count of running tasks\n\tinFlightTasks      map[string]string         // runID -> taskID\n\tinFlightTaskSet    map[string]map[string]bool // projectDir -> set of taskIDs in flight\n\t// ...\n}\n\ntype ProjectConfig struct {\n\tDir         string\n\tWorkflow    string\n\tConcurrency int\n\tTracker     ports.TaskTracker  // <-- Points to beads tracker\n\tEnabled     bool\n}\n```\n\n#### Main Orchestration Cycle: `Run()`\n**Lines:** 169-300\n\nThe orchestrator follows this algorithm:\n\n1. **Lock and Check State** (169-182):\n   - Get project config\n   - Calculate available concurrency slots: `available = Concurrency - inFlight[projectDir]`\n\n2. **Determine \"Ready Work\"** (188-191):\n   ```go\n   tasks, err := pc.Tracker.ListReady(ctx, projectDir)\n   ```\n   - Calls the task tracker's `ListReady()` to get open tasks with no blocking dependencies\n   - Ready tasks are returned sorted by priority (highest first)\n\n3. **Check Available Slots** (184-186):\n   ```go\n   if available <= 0 {\n       return 0, nil  // No capacity → return 0 dispatched\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Process Ready Tasks** (203-297):\n   For each ready task (up to `available` slots):\n   \n   a. **Skip if Already In-Flight** (207-213):\n   ```go\n   alreadyRunning := o.isTaskInFlight(projectDir, task.ID)\n   if alreadyRunning {\n       log.Printf(\"orchestrator: skipping task %s (already in flight)\", task.ID)\n       continue\n   }\n   ```\n   \n   b. **Claim the Task** (215-218):\n   ```go\n   if err := pc.Tracker.Claim(ctx, task.ID); err != nil {\n       log.Printf(\"orchestrator: failed to claim task %s: %v\", task.ID, err)\n       continue\n   }\n   ```\n   \n   c. **Two Execution Paths**:\n   \n   **Path A: Host Workflow** (220-272)\n   - If `.cloche/host.cloche` exists:\n     - Parse the workflow\n     - Execute it with `HostRunner.RunWorkflow()`\n     - Increment `inFlight[projectDir]` and track task\n     - Run in background goroutine\n   \n   **Path B: Fallback (Prompt → Dispatch)** (274-296)\n     - Generate prompt via `promptGen.Generate()`\n     - Dispatch run via `dispatch()` (which calls `srv.RunWorkflow()`)\n     - Increment `inFlight[projectDir]` and track task\n\n5. **Return Dispatched Count** (299):\n   ```go\n   return dispatched, nil\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **In-Flight Tracking**\n\n**Data Structures:**\n- `inFlight[projectDir]`: Integer count of running tasks per project\n- `inFlightTasks[runID]`: Maps run ID to task ID (for completion handling)\n- `inFlightTaskSet[projectDir][taskID]`: Set-like map for fast deduplication checks\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n```go\n// trackTask (lines 141-147): Record a new in-flight task\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) trackTask(projectDir, runID, taskID string) {\n\to.inFlightTasks[runID] = taskID\n\tif o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] == nil {\n\t\to.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] = make(map[string]bool)\n\t}\n\to.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir][taskID] = true\n}\n\n// untrackTask (lines 150-157): Remove when task completes\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) untrackTask(projectDir, runID string) string {\n\ttaskID := o.inFlightTasks[runID]\n\tdelete(o.inFlightTasks, runID)\n\tif taskID != \"\" && o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] != nil {\n\t\tdelete(o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir], taskID)\n\t}\n\treturn taskID\n}\n\n// isTaskInFlight (lines 160-165): Check if task is already running (deduplication)\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) isTaskInFlight(projectDir, taskID string) bool {\n\tif set := o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir]; set != nil {\n\t\treturn set[taskID]\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n\n// InFlight (lines 353-357): Public method to query current in-flight count\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) InFlight(projectDir string) int {\n\to.mu.Lock()\n\tdefer o.mu.Unlock()\n\treturn o.inFlight[projectDir]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Concurrency Limit Determination**\n\nThe orchestrator determines \"ready work\" based on:\n\n1. **Available Concurrency Slots**:\n   ```\n   available = ProjectConfig.Concurrency - inFlight[projectDir]\n   ```\n   - If `available <= 0`, no new tasks are dispatched (returns 0)\n\n2. **Task Readiness** (from beads tracker):\n   - Tasks must have status == \"open\"\n   - All blocking dependencies must be \"closed\"\n   - No in-flight task with the same ID (deduplication)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Beads Task Tracker**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go`\n\nThe tracker manages open tasks in `.beads/issues.jsonl`:\n\n```go\ntype Tracker struct {\n\tprojectDir string\n\tmu         sync.Mutex\n}\n\n// ListReady returns open tasks whose blocking dependencies are all closed\nfunc (t *Tracker) ListReady(ctx context.Context, project string) ([]ports.TrackerTask, error) {\n\t// 1. Read all issues from .beads/issues.jsonl\n\tissues, err := readIssuesFromFile(t.beadsPath())\n\t\n\t// 2. Build status lookup\n\tstatusByID := make(map[string]string, len(issues))\n\tfor _, iss := range issues {\n\t\tstatusByID[iss.ID] = iss.Status\n\t}\n\t\n\t// 3. Filter: open status + all dependencies closed\n\tvar tasks []ports.TrackerTask\n\tfor _, iss := range issues {\n\t\tif iss.Status != \"open\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tif hasOpenBlockers(iss, statusByID) {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\ttasks = append(tasks, ports.TrackerTask{...})\n\t}\n\t\n\t// 4. Sort by priority (highest first)\n\tsort.Slice(tasks, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\treturn tasks[i].Priority > tasks[j].Priority\n\t})\n\t\n\treturn tasks, nil\n}\n\n// Claim, Complete, Fail: Update task status by appending to JSONL\nfunc (t *Tracker) Claim(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error {\n\treturn t.appendStatusUpdate(taskID, \"in_progress\")\n}\n\nfunc (t *Tracker) Complete(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error {\n\treturn t.appendStatusUpdate(taskID, \"closed\")\n}\n\nfunc (t *Tracker) Fail(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error {\n\treturn t.appendStatusUpdate(taskID, \"open\")  // Retry\n}\n```\n\n**Port Interface:**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/tracker.go`\n\n```go\ntype TaskTracker interface {\n\tListReady(ctx context.Context, project string) ([]TrackerTask, error)\n\tClaim(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n\tComplete(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n\tFail(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Run Completion and Auto-Trigger**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` (lines 327-350)\n\nWhen a workflow run completes:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) OnRunComplete(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, runID string, state domain.RunState) {\n\t// 1. Untrack the task and decrement in-flight counter\n\to.mu.Lock()\n\tpc := o.projects[projectDir]\n\ttaskID := o.untrackTask(projectDir, runID)\n\tif o.inFlight[projectDir] > 0 {\n\t\to.inFlight[projectDir]--\n\t}\n\to.mu.Unlock()\n\n\t// 2. Update task status in tracker\n\tif taskID != \"\" && pc != nil {\n\t\tif state == domain.RunStateSucceeded {\n\t\t\