[2026-03-07T18:49:50Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SaWCiLCh2FEixHkU2xxRSB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly:\n\n- 4 tasks are `in_progress` (not `open`)\n- Only 1 task is `open`\n- `ListReady` filters for `status == \"open\"` only\n\nThe user says \"bd list shows 4 open, unblocked P2 tasks\". Looking at the data:\n- `cloche-9ea` - in_progress - \"Project versioning...\"\n- `cloche-r3b` - in_progress - \"Investigate cloche orchestrate...\" (this is the current task!)\n- `cloche-t62` - in_progress - \"Auto-rebuild stale containers...\"\n\n\n- `cloche-xyy` - in_progress - \"Simplify code agent switching...\"\n- `cloche-cxs` - open - \"Document Cloche installation options\"\n\nThe real problem is that when the daemon restarts or a run fails without properly completing, tasks stuck in `in_progress` never get reset back to `open` since the beads tracker operates independently of the daemon lifecycle.\n\nWhen the daemon starts fresh, the in-flight map is empty and `FailStaleRuns()` marks old runs as failed, but there's no logic to reset those stale `in_progress` tasks back to `open`. This means `ListReady()` only sees truly open tasks and misses the ones that are stuck, while the orchestrator's in-memory state has no knowledge of them either. The fix is to reconcile stale `in_progress` tasks during daemon startup—if a task is marked in-progress in beads but has no active run in the daemon, it should be reset to open.\n\nBut wait, let me reconsider this. When `initOrchestrator` creates a fresh orchestrator with empty in-flight maps, the tracker still has those stuck tasks. So there should be capacity available (concurrency minus zero in-flight), and `ListReady` should return open tasks like cloche-cxs. Yet the user reports no ready work found, which suggests either that task has blockers or something else is preventing it from being dispatched. The user also mentions bd list shows 4 open, unblocked P2 tasks, but my analysis shows 4 tasks are stuck in `in_progress`—there's a discrepancy I need to resolve.\n\nThe real issue is that `ListReady` only returns tasks with `status == \"open\"`, but previous daemon runs left tasks stuck in `in_progress`. The fix is to add a startup reconciliation step that either resets stale `in_progress` tasks back to open, or includes them in `ListReady` if they're not currently tracked by the orchestrator. The first approach is cleaner. I'll add a `RecoverStaleTasks` method to handle this on startup. I'm settling on adding a recovery method to the tracker that finds all stale `in_progress` tasks and resets them back to `open`, then calling it from `initOrchestrator` after each project is registered.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3002,"cache_read_input_tokens":37557,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3002},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36e135ce-10f3-4a37-be7d-4cf1fde5dba1","uuid":"3f7e61c1-a597-4dfd-ba79-abf14fdffc75"}
