[2026-03-07T18:49:50Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CFRUVwiaxvD2jEYYTiscRV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the root cause. Here's what's happening:\n\n**Root cause:** Tasks get stuck in `in_progress` status after daemon restart. When the orchestrator claims a task (changes status from `open` → `in_progress` in the JSONL file) but the daemon crashes or restarts before the run completes, those tasks remain `in_progress` forever. On restart:\n\n1. The daemon calls `store.FailStaleRuns()` to clean up DB runs — but this does NOT reset the beads tracker\n2. The orchestrator starts fresh with empty `inFlight` maps\n3. `ListReady()` only returns tasks with `status == \"open\"` — the stale `in_progress` tasks are skipped\n4. Result: \"No ready work found\" even though tasks exist\n\nCurrent state confirms this: **4 tasks stuck in `in_progress`**, only 1 truly `open`.\n\nThe fix: Add a `RecoverStaleTasks` method to the `TaskTracker` interface and beads adapter, then call it during orchestrator startup to reset `in_progress` tasks back to `open` when there are no corresponding in-flight runs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1450,"cache_read_input_tokens":40559,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1450},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36e135ce-10f3-4a37-be7d-4cf1fde5dba1","uuid":"232ada81-b65e-4e54-aa5a-3422b187c5c5"}
